The thrice-repeated verb ^piangere~ (weep) offered by
Beatrice in reproof to Dante echoes and rebukes the thrice-repeated
plangent calling of Virgil's name by Dante in vv. 49-51.
For a wide-ranging meditation on the possible references of Beatrice's
'sword,' see Wayne Storey, "The Other Sword of ^Purgatorio~ XXX,"
^Dante Studies~ 107 (1989), pp. 85-99.
..TCHR:
354
..AUTH:
